result.execSummary:
The defendant Sierra E Tart was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine to be paid in 90 days, or serve 7 days jail consecutive as penalty for non payment.

Defendant Sierra E Tart in court with attorney Adam J. Schleis.  Stephen Joseph Centinario appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Defendant has completed up front community service.  The State moves to amend the charge to a county ordinance of theft 13-102(c)(12).  The Court amends the charge accordingly.  A no contest plea is entered and the Court finds the Defendant guilty of the amended charge. The Defendant is sentenced as follows:  FINE: $330.50 to be paid in 90 days or Defendant to serve 7 days jail consecutive as penalty for failure to pay.
Filed by the State. Witness list attached.
